    "body": "fixes #22606\r\nfixes #23946 \r\nfixes #24417\r\nfixes #24450\r\ncloses #23898\r\n\r\nModifications:\r\n- [x] Extend bootstrapping capabilities to use buildcaches\r\n- [x] Allow to configure the order of methods tried for bootstrapping from configuration files\r\n- [x] Allow to trust or untrust bootstrapping methods from cli\r\n- [x] Add a command to list all known bootstrapping methods and their trust levels\r\n- [ ] Bootstrap from binaries in GA linux tests\r\n- [ ] Add documentation on the new `spack bootstrap` subcommands\r\n\r\nTo try this PR on `x86-64`, `aarch64` or `ppc64le` machines:\r\n```console\r\n$ cd <mirror-dir>\r\n$ wget https://github.com/alalazo/spack-bootstrap-mirrors/releases/download/v0.1-rc.2/bootstrap-buildcache.tar.gz\r\n$ tar xzvf bootstrap-buildcache.tar.gz\r\n\r\n$ # Change the url of the `github-actions` method to the mirror above\r\n$ vi $spack/etc/spack/defaults/bootstrap.yaml \r\n\r\n$ cd <spack-repo>\r\n$ git fetch upstream pull/22720/head:PR/22720\r\n$ git checkout PR/22720\r\n```\r\nAt that point you should be able to do something like:\r\n```console\r\n$ spack find -b\r\n==> Showing internal bootstrap store at \"/home/culpo/.spack/bootstrap/store\"\r\n==> 0 installed packages\r\n\r\n$ spack bootstrap list\r\n[ shows list of known bootstrapping methods ]\r\n$ spack bootstrap trust github-actions\r\n$ spack bootstrap list\r\n[ \"github-actions\" now is TRUSTED ]\r\n\r\n$ spack solve zlib\r\n==> Best of 0 answers.\r\n==> Optimization: [0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0]\r\nzlib@1.2.11%gcc@10.1.0+optimize+pic+shared arch=linux-ubuntu18.04-broadwell\r\n\r\n$ spack find -b\r\n==> Showing internal bootstrap store at \"/home/culpo/.spack/bootstrap/store\"\r\n==> 2 installed packages\r\n-- linux-rhel5-x86_64 / gcc@9.3.0 -------------------------------\r\nclingo-bootstrap@spack  python@3.6\r\n```",
